<!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE (Langley) -->
<section id="local" style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#f9f8f6">
  <div style="max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:.5rem"><span class="section-label">Local Knowledge</span></div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align:center">Injury &amp; ICBC Claims in Langley: What to Know</h2>
    <p style="text-align:center;max-width:680px;margin:1rem auto 0;color:var(--muted);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65">Langley sits at the eastern edge of Metro Vancouver, where the Trans-Canada and busy commuter routes put many residents in collisions every year. If you have been hurt in or around Langley, here is the local context that shapes your claim.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(250px,1fr));gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2.5rem">
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.15rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">Where Langley crashes happen</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Highway 1 (the Trans-Canada), the Langley Bypass, Fraser Highway, and 200 Street carry the area's heaviest traffic, while the 208 Street and Glover Road corridors and the Highway 1 interchanges are frequent collision points. Rain and fog are common factors.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.15rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">ICBC &amp; your claim</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Most BC auto injuries run through ICBC, whose Enhanced Care system provides medical and wage benefits regardless of fault. We make sure ICBC pays the full benefits you are owed, challenge denials and low offers, and pursue every additional claim the law still allows. Under BC's Limitation Act you generally have <strong>2 years</strong> to act.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.15rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">Getting treated</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Serious injuries in the Langley area are first treated at Langley Memorial Hospital, with major trauma transferred to Royal Columbian Hospital in New Westminster. Keep every medical record and receipt, they are central to proving your claim.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

